	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Drag wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Battletoads used a similar technique to get parallax scrolling in certain stages (like the cave level).<br /><br />Same with Metal Storm, except Metal Storm did it with CHR bankswitching instead of CHR-RAM!</div><br /><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wfh9VOCqnmU#t=3m03s" class="postlink">Mitsume ga Tooru</a> is another example (I'm pretty sure it uses bankswitching too), but the effect is not so good in that game. The shadows, which are supposed to be projected on the background plane moves along with the foreground, which looks weird.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Zepper wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Ok, so what's the red and green thing?</div>
<br />Red indicates background, green indicates sprites. First, the image is shown normally, then the same footage is shown using the color coding. The consoles that have more planes use other colors to represent those planes.

		

